    <description>
        <p><b>What’s ZapZap?</b></p>
        <p>ZapZap is a container for executing WhatsApp Web, functioning as a WebApp. This means that all features 
           available in WhatsApp Web are supported, along with additional integrations that enhance the system experience.</p>
        
        <p><b>Key Features:</b></p>
        <ul>
            <li>Support for multiple accounts.</li>
            <li>Background execution.</li>
            <li>Built-in spell checker.</li>
            <li>System theme-based customizations.</li>
        </ul>

        <p><b>Data Security:</b></p>
        <p>ZapZap does not modify or interfere with WhatsApp Web’s execution. All source code is open and 
           publicly available on GitHub for auditability.</p>

        <p><b>About:</b></p>
        <p>Originally developed for personal use, ZapZap was later shared so that others could benefit from 
           a more system-integrated WhatsApp client.</p>
    </description>

